Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js
==============================================

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the App Router Next.js project.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.6.1) to the project
- Command used: `npm install @vercel/analytics --legacy-peer-deps`
- The `--legacy-peer-deps` flag was necessary due to peer dependency conflicts with Svelte packages that are optional dependencies

### 2. Modified Files

#### app/layout.tsx
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `{children}` element
- This placement ensures analytics tracking is enabled across all pages in the application

#### package.json
- Added `"@vercel/analytics": "^1.6.1"` to dependencies

#### package-lock.json
- Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics and its dependencies

## Verification Completed:

✓ Build completed successfully - `npm run build` passed without errors
✓ Linter executed - No new errors introduced (existing errors were pre-existing)
✓ Tests passed - All 31 tests across 4 test files passed successfully

## Implementation Notes:

- This is an App Router project (uses `app` directory structure)
- The Analytics component was placed in the root layout file to enable tracking across the entire application
- The component is lightweight and won't affect page performance
- Analytics will automatically start collecting data when the application is deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box

## Next Steps:

Once deployed to Vercel, analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab for this project.
